The paper deals with the treedepth measure, which is a graph parameter related to tree decompositions and elimination trees. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper presents algorithms for deciding treedepth, which involves graph coloring and other combinatorial techniques, indicating that it could also be classified under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper mentions chordal graphs, which are a subclass of perfect graphs, suggesting a possible classification under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
